  "prompt": "What are some tips for investing $2,000?",
  "response": "Here are some tips for investing $2,000:\n\n1. Emergency Fund First\n- Consider setting aside some money in a high-yield savings account\n- Aim for 3-6 months of living expenses\n\n2. Low-Cost Index Funds\n- Invest in broad market index funds with low fees\n- Examples: S&P 500 index funds, total stock market funds\n- Good for long-term, diversified growth\n\n3. Retirement Accounts\n- Max out 401(k) if employer matching is available\n- Open an IRA (Traditional or Roth)\n- Tax advantages and potential long-term growth\n\n4. Robo-Advisors\n- Automated investment platforms\n- Low minimum investment requirements\n- Diversified portfolios based on risk tolerance\n\n5. Individual Stocks\n- Research and invest in quality, established companies\n- Consider dividend-paying stocks\n- Diversify across sectors\n\n6. ETFs (Exchange Traded Funds)\n- Diversified, low-cost investment vehicles\n- Provide exposure to multiple companies/sectors\n- Easier to trade than mutual funds\n\n7. Fractional Investing\n- Invest small amounts in expensive stocks\n- Platforms like Robinhood, Stash offer this option\n\n8. Consider Risk Tolerance\n- Balance potential returns with personal risk comfort level\n\nRemember to do research and possibly consult a financial advisor.",
